abstract: >
  Parallel Mirror Steer-by-Wire is an open-source research platform developed at the MOME Robotics Studio to investigate embodied human–robot interaction and adaptive robotics through Research through Design methodologies. The repository documents a wireless bilateral motor interface in which twoESP32-based BLDC motor nodes exchange angular position data over ESP-NOW andgenerate mutual spring-like resistance through local torque control. Builtwith the SimpleFOC ecosystem, magnetic angle sensing, and low-cost embeddedhardware, the prototype supports reproducible experimentation with hapticreciprocity, steer-by-wire coupling, and embodied physical interaction.
